docs.lead_paragraph: As temperatures dip health officials said the cold could lead to other health problems, including a worsening of heart and lung diseases and an increase in anxiety and depression.

headline.seo: Hypothermia and Carbon Monoxide Poisoning Cases Soar in New York After Hurricane Sandy
headline.main: Hypothermia and Carbon Monoxide Poisoning Cases Soar in City After Hurricane
headline.print_headline: Hypothermia and Carbon Monoxide Poisoning Cases Soar in City After Hurricane

docs.abstract: Health officials send alert to thousands of doctors and other health care providers that  number of cold-exposure cases in New York City tripled in weeks following Hurricane Sandy compared with same period in previous years; cold could lead to worsening of heart and lung diseases and increase in anxiety and depression.
docs.snippet: As temperatures dip health officials said the cold could lead to other health problems, including a worsening of heart and lung diseases and an increase in anxiety and depression.
